Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.08,0:00:05.84,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Uru of the Ninth Garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.26,0:00:08.42,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,the Abyssal Shaft's final raid boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.11,0:00:10.80,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If this had turned into a fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.80,0:00:13.99,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,even all of Silver Sword working \Ntogether couldn't beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.09,0:00:16.24,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.37,0:00:20.71,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The only difference is the color of his collar patch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:23.29,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to tell them apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.37,0:00:25.90,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Kunie Clan...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.08,0:00:33.20,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Of course... He's frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.13,0:00:36.88,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times we \Ndie, we keep coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.88,0:00:38.48,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's like some zombie attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.45,0:00:41.22,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If something like that attacked me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.70,0:00:44.80,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even still, he stands against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.22,0:00:46.32,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,For pride?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.93,0:00:50.61,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,A strong will to protect Yamato \Nand the People of the Land?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.60,0:01:00.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.95,0:01:02.58,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.03,0:01:10.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just one left!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.64,0:01:11.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.51,0:01:19.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.57,0:01:27.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to speak to Kinjou.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.19,0:01:32.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You have reached this place. \NIt is our duty to speak with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:11.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how the flow of gold coins works?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.75,0:03:13.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:17.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,In accordance with the contract, \Nwe share this information with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.67,0:03:22.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,All gold coins in Yamato are \Nborn here and return here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.30,0:03:25.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The coins flow by means of ancient technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.88,0:03:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which even we do not understand or control.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.58,0:03:35.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The coins are distributed to dungeons \Nand monsters from this massive stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.15,0:03:39.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This structure is a secret hidden \Nin the darkness of Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.58,0:03:45.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For centuries, the Kunie have kept it secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:52.00,Title,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1779,1)}The Gold of the Kunie
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.07,0:03:50.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Gold of the Kunie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.05,0:03:56.50,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The system that gives gold coins to monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:04:01.83,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,To those of us who knew this as \Na game, it was just a system,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.83,0:04:04.62,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,so we can understand that it isn't good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:06.01,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.46,0:04:08.86,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,What would People of the \NLand, who have fought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.86,0:04:11.51,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,and been tormented by \Nmonsters for so long, think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.38,0:04:16.41,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible they might even consider \Nthis a betrayal by the Kunie Clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.24,0:04:18.91,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Of course the Kunie are concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.75,0:04:21.55,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't thought that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.02,0:04:26.16,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We have no intention of telling anyone the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about this zone or even of its existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:33.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You have reached this place, and according \Nto the law passed down for generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.09,0:04:35.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,you have the right to take the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.50,0:04:40.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Throughout the centuries, \Npart of the law has been lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.20,0:04:44.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We do not know if you have the right
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.65,0:04:47.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,to take a thousand gold pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.65,0:04:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or a hundred million.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:53.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But the legends impart our ancestors' words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:56.51,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.73,0:04:58.56,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But even so,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.28,0:05:01.32,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,there's someone I want to let win.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.81,0:05:03.07,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I want to repay everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.77,0:05:04.78,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.78,0:05:07.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Kunie's gold brings both fortune and disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.40,0:05:10.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A great treasure is no treasure at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.86,0:05:15.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Beware, for the beast you keep \Nwill destroy the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:21.77,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,What I couldn't say to Kinjou...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:24.30,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,What I really wanted to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.10,0:05:43.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.44,0:05:46.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The contract has been made and completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.48,0:05:49.66,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Round Table does not seek wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:54.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even need the rights to the Guild Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:06:01.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We now have the power to live \Npeacefully in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.43,0:06:05.40,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We thank the system that gave us this chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.01,0:06:08.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,but that time is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.65,0:06:11.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even if another problem occurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:18.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've reached the conclusion that it \Nshould be resolved another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:24.19,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This contract spell is completed \Nwhen it is made and torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.73,0:06:28.57,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We assign all rights for the city of Akihabara
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.57,0:06:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,including the Guild Hall, Cathedral, \Nand merchant facilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:33.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,to the Yamato server.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.26,0:06:37.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And through the destruction of the contract,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:38.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,we make this assignation of rights eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.35,0:06:44.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We purchased Akihabara's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.63,0:06:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,primary facilities to prevent their misuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.61,0:06:50.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But the cost of their maintenance
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.30,0:06:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was straining the Round Table's budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.29,0:06:55.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That was why I asked for financing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.94,0:06:57.71,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,After examining a number of possibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.71,0:06:59.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,and debating the matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.92,0:07:02.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,this expedition was my decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.18,0:07:07.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then, these coins were the funds \Nused to purchase these rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.27,0:07:09.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:13.16,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,All gold coins are born here \Nand return here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.64,0:07:15.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Now that the contract is fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.30,0:07:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it has been exchanged for the \Nreturn of the gold we spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.65,0:07:19.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,All as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.84,0:07:24.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You came here to explain this to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.16,0:07:26.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,In a sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.27,0:07:29.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you discuss financing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.64,0:07:31.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's the critical issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:36.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We wish to purchase every field zone in Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.52,0:07:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The forests, mountains, and lakes. Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.34,0:07:43.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Every field zone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.70,0:07:46.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And as we just did, we will reassign their rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.40,0:07:52.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, we'd like to get rid of \Npurchasable zones altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.64,0:07:57.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,To prevent your enemies from owning them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.98,0:07:59.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.07,0:08:04.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Adventurers can purchase zones, \Nbut the People of the Land can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.62,0:08:10.65,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That is unfair, and we believe it may \Nbecome a problem in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.81,0:08:15.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not denying the ownership of property.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.10,0:08:19.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe contracts between \Npeople will suffice for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.23,0:08:22.87,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So please lend us the money to do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.51,0:08:26.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,so we will not destroy ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.72,0:08:29.57,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Give us money, so we can return it to this flow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.39,0:08:35.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yamato's land should be returned to Yamato!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:41.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I do owe you all a debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.75,0:08:57.85,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We won.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.09,0:09:05.36,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.36,0:09:06.85,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.43,0:09:13.36,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,My friends are amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.93,0:09:16.36,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They really are amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.64,0:09:17.78,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,We won.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:19.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we won!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.49,0:09:21.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We won.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.60,0:09:29.11,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(292,1)\fs20\an7}Eye of Lynceus
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.69,0:09:31.12,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(292,1)\fs20\an4}Fire-eating Ice Blade
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.69,0:09:31.12,HUD1-2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(292,1)}Uroboros Scale
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.50,0:09:34.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Those are items from the two raid bosses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.63,0:09:37.27,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Look at all the phantasm-class items...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.82,0:09:40.61,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The rule is that, when we first beat a raid boss,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.61,0:09:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the guild master chooses who gets the items.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.35,0:09:48.15,Flower,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(486,1)}Moon Blossom Talisman\N\N{\fs20}Effect/ Moon Blossom Talisman\N{\fs18}Reduces loss of experience points \Nwhen a player revives after dying. \NStrengthens defensive magic as well \Nas mental-attribute offensive magic.\N\N{\fs20}Legend/ Moon Blossom Talisman\N{\fs18}A phantasm-class talisman carved in \Nthe image of a flower that, according \Nto legend, blooms with the moon's \Ncycle. It is said to bless souls in transit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:53.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Moon Blossom Talisman!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.91,0:09:57.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to give this to the villain in glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.98,0:10:06.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.36,0:10:08.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The air changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:11.54,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It feels warmer, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.21,0:10:14.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he did something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.37,0:10:16.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.41,0:10:17.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a good item!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.69,0:10:21.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Its resistances and stat boosts are top notch!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.24,0:10:24.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So I am giving it to the villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.76,0:10:27.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't part of Silver Sword,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.15,0:10:29.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,but he's a comrade who fought with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.98,0:10:32.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Prometheus...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.78,0:10:33.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:56.46,SignA,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Encartanto \NVuoinen \NFederico \NDemikas
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.66,0:11:02.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Our names have been carved here for eternity!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:07.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We are the first adventurers \Nto ever clear this raid zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.09,0:11:16.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.16,0:11:18.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.60,0:11:19.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's over,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.64,0:11:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.47,0:11:28.72,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.18,0:11:30.95,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.46,0:11:32.51,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.11,0:11:37.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.57,0:11:42.54,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.54,0:11:44.18,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.18,0:11:46.89,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I can't decide what to wear!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.45,0:11:49.77,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Why not just wear what you always wear?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:52.12,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen him for over a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.12,0:11:54.77,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I want to welcome him in cute clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.77,0:11:57.29,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Cute clothes, cute clothes, cute clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:02.99,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You know that no matter what \Nyou wear, he'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.21,0:12:08.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Don't I look elegant?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.38,0:12:10.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.43,0:12:12.87,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressing up, Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.26,0:12:15.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The new members are also coming, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.53,0:12:18.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,As their superior, I have to look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.15,0:12:21.45,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Just go as you always are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.24,0:12:26.35,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Nyanta, shouldn't we get going?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.07,0:12:29.39,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's still too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:33.22,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.22,0:12:36.34,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They might get there early!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.34,0:12:37.91,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Minori.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:43.37,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You know my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.37,0:12:45.41,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He'll arrive right on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:47.79,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.79,0:12:49.91,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,She's a grown-up, so she isn't worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.48,0:13:04.09,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,After we cleared the raid,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.53,0:13:06.91,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,we returned to Susukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.19,0:13:12.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,On the way, I spoke about many things \Nwith the members of Silver Sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:15.88,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,What they've experienced since the Apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.88,0:13:17.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,What they've learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:21.88,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You damned enchanter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.53,0:13:24.03,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,say my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:33.87,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I never said his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:38.04,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, it feels like I avoided saying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.98,0:13:41.26,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It may have simply been self-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.86,0:13:45.21,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I remembered how powerless I \Nfelt right after the Apocalypse,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.71,0:13:50.54,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,and I took it out on him and his reckless \Nbehavior, since I could do nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.30,0:13:54.55,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Stealing someone's name is never all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.04,0:13:58.66,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It means you're unwilling to \Nrecognize them as human.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.13,0:14:00.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:02.18,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Demikas,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.18,0:14:03.94,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:07.57,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Me, neither, Shiroe of Log Horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.56,0:14:10.75,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,We were finally able to agree on something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.10,0:14:17.04,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,We agreed on the fact that we'd never agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:19.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You died?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.77,0:14:22.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You both died during the raid?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:30.05,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I w-want to go over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.59,0:14:33.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,He's been badgering us with \Nquestions since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.32,0:14:38.76,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Should I tell you what color panties \NI was wearing when I died?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.76,0:14:39.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.73,0:14:40.81,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.79,0:14:40.55,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't care
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.81,0:14:44.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well... What was it like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.52,0:14:46.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How did you come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:48.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the moment when you die—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.33,0:14:49.32,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I won't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.69,0:14:53.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You come, too, old guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.89,0:14:55.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not an old guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.75,0:14:59.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just let me... Let me talk to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:01.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let me talk to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.05,0:15:08.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I still need to investigate the \Ninter-city transport gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.13,0:15:10.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be heading back to Akihabara soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.90,0:15:12.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:15.52,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Silver Sword stayed in Susukino, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.06,0:15:20.46,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,They'll protect the town as they rebuild \Nand prepare for further raids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.28,0:15:28.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Add me to your friend list.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.31,0:15:33.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I already have.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.10,0:15:35.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.07,0:15:36.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.88,0:15:42.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how I saved Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.85,0:15:44.84,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right. That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.84,0:15:47.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What? Hey, it's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.69,0:15:53.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe really said, "Thank you, Mr. Demikas,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.42,0:15:55.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,with snot dripping from his nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:00.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.68,0:16:03.09,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You look much happier now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.58,0:16:06.94,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.81,0:16:19.98,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to ride with Naotsugu!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.98,0:16:23.68,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,My armor's heavy, so my griffin \Ndoesn't like to carry two people!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.58,0:16:27.15,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's just a special seat for someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.74,0:16:29.71,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,D-Definitely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.71,0:16:31.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tease him too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.57,0:16:35.30,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's no fun unless I tease him too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.30,0:16:37.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,When will you tell him
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you're a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:42.47,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Until he figures it out, it's a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.47,0:16:44.23,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's more fun that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.54,0:16:49.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a delicate time for Naotsugu with Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.48,0:16:53.68,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shiro! Why did you let her into the guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:55.24,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm an idol!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:57.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuhiko recommended her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.49,0:17:00.04,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just so we're clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.04,0:17:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't go to Susukino because Kazuhiko said to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.10,0:17:06.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.72,0:17:10.28,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You can save more people than I can, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.28,0:17:13.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Log Horizon isn't a charity, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.71,0:17:21.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But the world isn't going to \Nlet you stay uninvolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.80,0:17:23.52,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's a problem, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.51,0:17:27.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:34.56,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fad(356,1)}Kazuhiko \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NAssassin, Lv. 97 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.51,0:17:40.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Intix?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.80,0:17:44.77,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Zeldus, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:45.82,HUD1,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fad(405,1)}Mizufa Trudy {\fs20}\NRace/ Human \NWarlord, Lv. 68 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:48.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The princess is the same as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.88,0:17:48.83,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(396,1)}Zeldus \N{\fs20}Race/ People of the Law \NCleric, Lv. 90 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.08,0:17:52.33,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Every day is boring without the smell of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.33,0:17:54.08,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I'm going to rot away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.44,0:17:56.34,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,We have all the time in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.61,0:18:00.17,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait as long as it takes for battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.03,0:18:02.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that if we came here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.56,0:18:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all that could happen was that we could \Ndrink good alcohol, Person of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.35,0:18:08.15,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(362,1)}Nakalnard \N{\fs20}Race/ Wolf Fang \NGuardian, Lv. 93 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.56,0:18:12.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.53,0:18:15.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you would finish up quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:16.15,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fad(400,1)}Quon \N{\fs20}Race/ People of the Law \NBard, Lv. 90 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:22.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Did you stay up all night to \Nwatch the moon sink again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:23.16,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(355,1)}Jered Gun \N{\fs20}Race/ Elf \NArchmage, Lv. 36 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.36,0:18:27.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I was listening for voices calling me \Nfrom beyond the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.91,0:18:32.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No sign of the princess today, either, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:34.05,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(397,1)}Loreil Dawn \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NCleric, Lv. 41 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.34,0:18:40.53,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(402,960)}Intix \N{\fs20}Race/ Elf \NSorcerer, Lv. 90 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.96,0:18:42.80,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,So, what of Akihabara's army?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:46.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're continuing their conquest of Seventh Fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.13,0:18:49.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And that Royal Guard in Akihabara...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:51.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It seems he was captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.11,0:18:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One has reported thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.32,0:18:55.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A Royal Guard in Akihabara?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.21,0:18:59.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about? I wasn't told anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:01.15,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Do not worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.15,0:19:02.95,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:12.67,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The villain in glasses has returned to Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.95,0:19:19.39,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows what he was doing in Susukino?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:22.18,HUD1,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(402,1)}KR \N{\fs20}Race/ Elf \NSummoner, Lv. 92 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.12,0:19:22.18,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do, Intix?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:26.15,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The interference that doesn't \Nwork the way you expect is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.32,0:19:37.69,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Still, returning all the zones to Yamato, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:41.93,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think we'd have to go through \Nall that to accomplish it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.93,0:19:45.11,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it's been since the Tea Party, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.11,0:19:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.97,0:19:49.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,KR once told me that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.23,0:19:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was born under that sort of star, \Nand I should give up trying to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.11,0:19:57.01,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Are those the members of Log Horizon?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.56,0:19:58.62,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:01.09,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Marie!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.27,0:20:08.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, everyone! Thanks for \Ncoming to see me today!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.29,0:20:10.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the loud one?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.44,0:20:11.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Are you one to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.60,0:20:13.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's Tetra?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.43,0:20:14.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She's a girl, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.78,0:20:20.34,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, look... They're holding hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.96,0:20:23.11,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not like that, Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.11,0:20:25.77,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let me go! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.82,0:20:34.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.12,0:20:36.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We held down the fort for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.24,0:20:38.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We went to Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:43.40,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So we protected both Akihabara and Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.29,0:20:47.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.63,0:20:51.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.05,0:20:56.18,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.18,0:21:00.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,So, should we leave them alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.48,0:21:02.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who is this girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.22,0:21:04.86,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:07.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The brightest star shining in the night sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.49,0:21:11.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,the beautiful galactic idol, Tetra!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.97,0:21:13.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Call me "Tetra"!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.78,0:21:15.25,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Idol?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.66,0:21:18.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a guild master!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.47,0:21:21.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They seem busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:25.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll introduce you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.43,0:21:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.22,0:21:27.51,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.51,0:21:29.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.75,0:21:34.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Right on time, as I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.29,0:21:38.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get taller?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.33,0:21:39.80,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're terrible, my lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.80,0:21:41.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.79,0:21:44.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But somehow,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.60,0:21:48.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,you do seem a little more grown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.91,0:21:59.36,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be rude, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.36,0:22:01.40,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:03.08,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.08,0:22:04.67,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki was fighting, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.60,0:22:07.00,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Not only Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.42,0:22:08.53,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,All of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.27,0:22:10.89,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'm not with them...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.08,0:22:13.72,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we're far apart...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.74,0:22:17.28,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I can't see them...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.83,0:22:20.79,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is doing their best.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.80,0:22:23.51,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,All my companions are
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.85,0:22:26.24,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,charging forward with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.27,0:22:30.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.52,0:22:34.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.09,0:24:10.34,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Valentine's Day comes to \Nthe world of {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.80,0:24:14.09,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Even to those with no connection to it, \Nand those who don't want it to come.
